&#xa0;
[normal]Written evidence submitted by Alan Jordan, owner of Jordan Products Ltd (SRN 051)[bold]Having established my own design and manufacturing business in Ballyclare, Northern Ireland, I have worked with the Highways Agency (HA) since 2002 to develop a fully HA-approved 
[normal]mechanised system (Conemaster) to lift and lay traffic cones on the Strategic Road Network with new levels of speed, efficiency and safety. My reason for this submission is to set out how Conemaster can improve the network for all users and to draw on my o
[normal]wn experience with HA to illustrate the need for its reform. 
[normal]Conemaster is a British product which has been independently assessed by the International company Jacobs. It
[normal]’
[normal]s report in February 2012 accepted that Conemaster had the potential to save lives, 
[normal]to provide high value for money and to reduce congestion across the HA strategic road network. Despite being market ready and available since 2006, powerful vested interests working, in my view, with HA have ensured that Conemaster remains excluded from en
[normal]tering the home market. 
[normal]&#xa0;[bold]Executive Summary[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]i)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The approach to Road Worker Safety within the HA is in need of urgent and sweeping reform. The real picture regarding road worker incidents has been hidden for many years by systematic under-reporting. Recent fi
[normal]gures provide an alarming picture
[normal]*[bold].  
