[normal]The “Actions for Roads” paper says little about safety. It suggests, however, that continuous improvement seeks to develop, 
[normal]“technical innovations and behavioural measures to ensure road works are delivered safely”
[normal] :
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]the HA’s handling of 
[normal]Conemaster starkly illustrates that this is not part of the culture that exists in the HA or the industry today. There is unlikely to be a change in this direction without the Government (or the Committee) holding the HA (and its major contractors) more ro
[normal]bustly to account.
[normal] 
[normal](See section 3. below)[bold]&#xa0;
[normal]iii)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Action for roads states that 
[normal]“A single incident that closes a three-lane motorway for four hours can cost several million pounds in lost time, and there 
[normal]are some 80,000 incidents that impact at least one motorway 
[normal]lane each year.”
[normal] 
[normal](Source: Action for Roads - page47 sect3.44)
