[normal]vi)
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]It is a very serious question why, collectively, the HA and all its major contractors on the strategic road network have been able to turn 
[normal]their back on 
[normal]a technology which can provide greater efficiency, improve journey time reliability and reduce road worker casualties without any significant challenge by either Government or Parliament. Conemaster has been excluded from the market since 200
[normal]6, largely through the responses of the HA and its major contractors. In my view this has the appearance of some kind of cartel in operation. They have clearly all decided, possibly in concert, to reject investment in a technology which would bring conside
[normal]rable benefits to the public purse and to road users and road workers. Ministers, Parliament and taxpayers rightfully deserve higher standards from the HA especially in dealing with issues where the public interest is so clearly at stake. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]1.1
[normal] 
[normal]Safety represents only a small part of the “Action for Roads” document and has been omitte
[normal]d from the specific terms of reference for this enquiry but it is a major issue of public concern and should be an integral part of the work of this enquiry; Statutory reportable incidents involving road workers have grown by a staggering amount according 
[normal]to recent figures:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Mr Fitzpatrick M.P., in a PQ in September 2012 [120374], was informed that there was a total of 47 road worker injuries during 2011 on motorways. Over a 3 year period from 2009 – 2011 there were 2 fatalities involving road workers on mo
[normal]torways.
[normal] 
[normal]http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201213/cmhansrd/cm120912/text/120912w0001.htm[bold] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]-
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]however, a recent press release from the HA states 
[normal]that:
[normal] “[bold]Eight road workers have been killed in the last three years and during the last 12 months there have been 1747 incidents where road workers were injured while improving and maintaining the strategic road network in England.”
[normal] 
[normal]Source:HA press release [bold]21 Oct 2013. [bold]http://www.highways.gov.uk/news/press-releases/road-worker-tells-how-drunk-driver-careered-towards-them-on-the-m1/[bold] 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]How can one account for this staggering increase? Was there systematic under-reporting for many years and, if so, why? Has there been a huge increase in recent times and why?[bold]&#xa0;
